name: Nana Yōkai Collection: Tengu
description: Nana Yōkai Collection is a series of illustrations, created with the aim of sharing traditional Japanese mythology. In this series, Nana will be personifying herself as different Yōkai (Japanese spirits). This one is Tengu, also considered demigods, live in mountains and forests. People say that Tengu was actually part of the Yamabushi, mountain ascetic hermits who had acquired a magical and spiritual power.
